==English==
===Noun===
'''platinum group'''

# In chemistry a  group of [[element]]s with related properties similar to that of [[platinum]]. notably high resistance to chemical activity.  The platinumgroup consists of the elements [[ruthenium]], [[rhodium]], [[palladium]], [[osmium]], [[iridium]], and [[platinum]].   In the [[periodic table of elements]] they are in period 5 or 6 and in groups 8, 9 or 10.